GLOBAL
- The Conclave legacy: every city participated in the condemned-labor apparatus;
  none has formally admitted it; this unacknowledged guilt shapes current
  factional politics in all five cities
- The five cities are rivals but not at war; they cooperate on road warden
  funding and disaster relief when it serves them; they compete on trade routes
  and political influence
~
MIDGAARD
- CONTINUITY FACTION: preserve existing systems; maintain institutional records
  as they are; argue the Unindexed Years were accidental loss, not deliberate
- RECKONING FACTION: demand exposure of buried records including Midgaard's
  role in the Conclave condemned-labor chain; searching for original Unindexed
  Year ledgers; believe the Breach Tower holds duplicate copies
- Three civic oaths: "No ward unlit, no traveler uncounted." "No judgment
  hidden, no sentence unrecorded." "No levy taken that cannot be borne."
  All violated in practice. Both factions cite these oaths for opposite ends.
- Foundational power split still active: River Factors, Upland Syndicate,
  Temple Compact — their interests shape all major policy debates
~
KOWLOON
- Five institutions: no one rules alone; each can censure the others; the
  balance is the system; disrupting it is the goal of every faction below
- RIVER CORSAIRS (Captain Blacktide Shen): disgraced Ferry Masters heir; probes
  gate timings; wants to restore Tahn-Rei house influence over Harbor Syndics
- SALT COURT EXILES (Duchess Yuen Ahi): fund debt rings in southern quarter
  exploiting a legal flaw in how founding houses merged; long-game strategy
- ASH CULT: cells throughout the city; sabotage floodworks; ideologically
  anti-Covenant; have popular support in wards hardest hit by past floods
- JADE EELS: smuggling syndicate embedded in Harbor Syndics; believed to hold
  a Syndic seat; three investigations closed without result
~
KIESS
- THREE-POWER BALANCE: Compact Temples / Trade Syndics / Wall Command; each
  holds a tribunal seat; Executioner at the Central Prism is the enforcement
  mechanism binding all three to the compact
- Kiess's charter repudiation of sealed warrants is the city's primary
  political identity; it creates ongoing tension with Rakuen (whose emergency
  labor drafts look uncomfortably like sealed-warrant governance) and with
  Midgaard (whose Reckoning faction wants the same outcome but differently)
- Serathi sky-road corridor agreements: Trade Syndics in negotiations with
  Serathi over access to pre-Evermeet roost-chronicles; politically sensitive
~
RAKUEN
- AMENDMENT TRACK: petition Midgaard for annexation or formal recognition a
  fourth time; most institutionally supported but viewed as naive after three
  refusals
- QUIET SEPARATISTS: build independence through trade ties with Mafdet, Kowloon,
  and Kiess; active commercial negotiations ongoing; the realistic path forward
- PRESERVATION COALITION: hold the Southward Compact unamended; force Midgaard
  to confront what it pushed south for generations; ideologically principled
- All three factions block each other; the political result is stasis dressed
  as deliberation; the city calls itself paradise and runs emergency protocols
~
MAFDET
- QUAY CONCORD: senior captains and Harbor Wardens; maritime reliability above
  inland politics; they run the city in practical terms
- RED SAND ACCOUNTS: buy distressed inland debts cheap, convert to maritime
  obligations, enforce through Mafdet courts; technically legal; politically
  despised; they have the Strandline Compact's due-process on their side
- JACKAL SYNOD: claims universal funerary and oath-jurisdiction across the
  eastern corridor; Shrine of the First Claw rejects this claim; the Synod
  never had enough Mafdet presence to challenge directly; tension persists
- STRAND REMEMBERERS: hold pre-Fracture cartographic and navigational knowledge;
  beginning to sell to Kowloon and Kiess; this is increasingly politically
  significant as cities want pre-Keeper survey data
~
